  "body": "There is no `name` field specified in the following ABI which raises the exception:\r\n`INVALID_ARGUMENT: invalid type (argument=\"type\", value=\"u\", code=INVALID_ARGUMENT, version=abi/5.0.7)`\r\n\r\nI extract the ABI as follows and make the call over MetaMask:\r\n```\r\n  const MyToken = await hre.ethers.getContractFactory(\"MyToken\");\r\n  const MyAbi = MyToken.interface.format(\"json\");\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n  {\r\n    \"type\": \"function\",\r\n    \"name\": \"allowance\",\r\n    \"constant\": true,\r\n    \"stateMutability\": \"view\",\r\n    \"payable\": false,\r\n    \"inputs\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"address\",\r\n        \"name\": \"owner\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"address\",\r\n        \"name\": \"spender\"\r\n      }\r\n    ],\r\n    \"outputs\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"uint256\"\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI compared the truffle generated ABI and found out that they add an empty `name` field even if it is not specified and when I manually added the `name` field to the ABI it worked.\r\n```\r\n  {\r\n    \"type\": \"function\",\r\n    \"name\": \"allowance\",\r\n    \"constant\": true,\r\n    \"stateMutability\": \"view\",\r\n    \"payable\": false,\r\n    \"inputs\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"address\",\r\n        \"name\": \"owner\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"address\",\r\n        \"name\": \"spender\"\r\n      }\r\n    ],\r\n    \"outputs\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"type\": \"uint256\",\r\n        \"name\": \"\"\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nCould you please fix this with your generated ABIs to be more compatible?",
